TY  - JOUR
T1  - Influence Of Quality Of Work Life On Company And Union Commitment
AU  - Fields, Mitchell W.
AU  - Thacker, James W.
Y1  - 1992/06/01
PY  - 1992
DA  - 1992/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256382
DO  - 10.5465/256382
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 439
EP  - 450
VL  - 35
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - This study examined changes in union and organizational commitment after the implementation of a joint union-management quality-of-work-life (QWL) program. The results indicated that company commitment increased only when participants perceived the QWL effort as successful, but union commitment increased irrespective of the perception of QWL success.
AB  - This study examined changes in union and organizational commitment after the implementation of a joint union-management quality-of-work-life (QWL) program. The results indicated that company commitment increased only when participants perceived the QWL effort as successful, but union commitment increased irrespective of the perception of QWL success.
